S. Korea Says Overseas Investors’ Bond Holdings Rose in April

-- B y   S e y o o n   K i m
-- 
2011-05-03T21:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/s-korea-says-overseas-investors-bond-holdings-rose-in-april.html
South Korea  said overseas investors’
net holdings of the nation’s bonds climbed for a third month in
April on purchases from Germany and  China . Foreigners’ stock
holdings also increased, reversing a decline in March.  Bonds held by overseas investors increased by a net 1.13
trillion won ($1.06 billion), the biggest jump in six months, to
76.2 trillion won as of April 30, South Korea’s  Financial
Supervisory Service  said in an e-mailed statement today.  German investors were the biggest buyers of bonds in April,
with their holdings rising by a net 395 billion won, followed by
China, with a net gain of 333 billion won, according to the
statement.  Thailand  was the biggest seller, with net sales of
661.2 billion won, the regulator said.  Overseas investors purchased a net 4.4 trillion won of
South Korean stocks in April, boosting their net holdings to
412.5 trillion won, the regulator said.  Investors from Luxembourg were the biggest buyers of South
Korean stocks, with net purchases of 1 trillion won, the
statement showed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Seyoon Kim in Seoul at 
 skim7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
